This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D shape analysis and learning global features from multiple views. It also involves deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel deep neural network architecture for learning global features from part-level information. 

The paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with 3D shape analysis and segmentation. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves deep learning and the development of a novel neural network architecture. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves the use of a multi-attention mechanism for aggregating detected parts.
